cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL, cs.CV 

The paper discusses a new model for neural networks with external memory that emulates human working memory. This involves attention control in memory, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions that the model learns to have fine control over memory, which involves language processing and understanding. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions that the model successfully generalizes to longer sequences, which involves computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible sub-category.
